    "This research is highly linked with the point above on bias and fairness in LLMs, and therefore both could be studied jointly by looking at the reduction of biases and harm.",
    "Some systems, such as OpenAI's ChatGPT, acknowledge the risk of producing offensive content in their terms of service: \"Our Services may provide incomplete, incorrect, or offensive Output that does not represent OpenAIs views.",
    "If Output references any third party products or services, it doesnt mean the third party endorses or is affiliated with OpenAI.\"",
    "LLMs can also capture sensitive information retrieved from its training data.",
    "While this information is encoded in embeddings which are not human readable, it has been found (Pan et al., 2020) that an adversarial user can reverse engineer those embeddings to recover the sensitive information, which can have damaging consequences for the relevant individuals."
